<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,152,1084]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="BMNH" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
Senior White (1922) described this species from a single specimen that is now deposited in the 
<collectionCode box="[1341,1433,826,852]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">BMNH</collectionCode>
. He misinterpreted the sex of the 
<typeStatus box="[549,652,865,891]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">holotype</typeStatus>
describing it as a male. Actually it is a female. Currently, in the 
<typeStatus box="[151,254,904,930]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">holotype</typeStatus>
the postpedicel and style are lost from both antennae; otherwise it is in good condition
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
