<subSubSection pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,152,1084]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,312,981,1007]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Remarks</emphasis>
. The relationships of 
<taxonomicName box="[569,742,981,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plumicornis">
<emphasis box="[569,742,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. plumicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear beyond inclusion within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1221,1379,981,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biuncinata">
<emphasis box="[1221,1379,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">E. biuncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, primarily due to the presence of a long upturned bristle just above the fore coxa and squamiform setae on abdominal tergite 3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
